issues.issue_body:
### Steps to reproduce the problem

1. Follow some account on bsky.brid.gy
2. Wait for  `ActivityPub::SynchronizeFeaturedCollectionWorker`
3.
...


### Expected behaviour

Collects featured collection as well

### Actual behaviour

Failed with Invalid scheme format

### Detailed description

On sidekiq log:
```Addressable::URI::InvalidURIError: Invalid scheme format: '{"orderedItems" => ["https'```

### Mastodon instance

qdon.space

### Mastodon version

v4.4.0-alpha.5

### Technical details

If this is happening on your own Mastodon server, please fill out those:
- Ruby version: (from `ruby --version`, eg. v3.4.1)
- Node.js version: (from `node --version`, eg. v20.18.0)

Mastodon expects that `featured` to be URL string. But bsky bridge returns as object

